2.6DR Grade Prediction
Once the ordinal outputs are aggregated, the model assigns a final DR grade. There are five possible outcomes: No DR, Mild, Moderate, Severe, and Proliferative DR. The idea here is not to replace the ophthalmologist but to provide a reliable second opinion that can support clinical decision-making and streamline the screening process. Figure 3 illustrates the overall architecture of the proposed dual-resolution attention-based framework.

